# Morpheme Coordinate Transforms

Affixes as coordinate deltas. Not yet in walker — design phase.


## Principle

Parts of speech = dominant dimension (from mind/language):
  noun=μ, verb=τ, adj=φ, adverb=φ+τ, preposition=χ, pronoun=μ+φ

Affixes shift coordinates predictably:
  verb → noun = +μ (add substance)
  noun → adj = +φ (add quality)
  present → past = +τ (add time)
  negation = flip φ (invert quality)


## Suffix Rules

  -tion/-sion/-ment/-ness/-ity  verb/adj → noun    +μ
  -able/-ible/-ous/-ful/-al     noun/verb → adj     +φ
  -less                         noun → adj (lacking) -φ
  -ed                           present → past       +τ
  -ing                          ongoing              +τ+μ
  -er/-or/-ist                  verb → agent noun    +μ (ist: +μ+φ)
  -ly                           adj → adverb         +φ
  -ize/-ise/-ify                noun/adj → verb      +τ
  -s/-es                        singular → plural    +μ


## Prefix Rules

  un-/dis-/im-/in-/non-/mis-   negation             flip φ
  anti-                         antimatter           flip all signs
  re-                           repetition           +τ
  pre-                          before               +2τ
  post-                         after                -2τ
  out-/inter-                   outward/between      +χ
  trans-                        across               +2χ
  sub-                          below                -χ
  super-                        above                +2χ+φ
  co-                           together             +μ
  over-/under-                  excess/deficit        ±μ


## Status

Table derived from English morphology. Consistent with dimensional
semantics. Not tested cross-linguistically. Implementation: strip
affix, apply delta to root coordinate. Dissolves into wave byte
processing in the walker.
